# Git commit and push discipline

**Agent commits proactively** after meaningful milestones — do not wait for the user to say "commit".

**Agent pushes** when unpushed commit count reaches **10**, or when the user explicitly asks to push.

## When to commit

Commit after:

- ✅ An **approved implementation phase** completes and validates
- ✅ A **feature** or user-visible capability is done
- ✅ A **bug fix** is verified
- ✅ A **refactor** that preserves behavior is complete
- ✅ **Docs** tied to shipped work (README, ADR, phase report)

Do **not** commit:

- ❌ Mid-phase WIP with failing tests or broken build
- ❌ Plan-only changes before user approval (unless docs-only plan)
- ❌ Files containing secrets — warn user instead
- ❌ Trivial one-line nits unless bundled with the same milestone commit

## Conventional commit format

```
type(scope): imperative summary

Optional body: why this change, not a file list.
```

| Type | Use |
|------|-----|
| `feat` | New capability |
| `fix` | Bug fix |
| `refactor` | Behavior-preserving restructure |
| `docs` | Documentation only |
| `test` | Tests only |
| `chore` | Tooling, deps, config |
| `perf` | Performance improvement |

Examples:

```
feat(billing): add Stripe webhook handler for subscription events
fix(auth): reject expired refresh tokens before DB lookup
docs(readme): add architecture diagram and env reference
```

## Commit workflow

1. Validate the milestone (tests/lint/typecheck as project supports)
2. Update `PROGRESS.md` and phase report if present
3. `git status` + `git diff` — review staged scope
4. Stage relevant files only — no secrets, no unrelated changes
5. Commit with conventional message
6. Run **push check** (below)
7. Report: **hash**, **message**, **unpushed count**, **push result** if pushed

## Push policy

Push after **every commit** when either:

- Unpushed commits on current branch **≥ 10**, or
- User explicitly says **push** (now or in global rules)

### Push check (run after every commit)

```powershell
# Commits ahead of upstream (0 if no upstream yet)
git rev-list --count @{u}..HEAD 2>$null
# If no upstream, count all commits not on origin/<branch>:
git rev-list --count origin/<branch>..HEAD 2>$null
```

| Condition | Action |
|-----------|--------|
| Unpushed ≥ 10 | `git push` (use `-u origin <branch>` if no upstream) |
| User asked to push | `git push` immediately, even if < 10 |
| Unpushed < 10 | Do not push; tell user count (e.g. "3/10 until auto-push") |
| No remote | Skip push; tell user to add remote |
| On `main`/`master` | Push allowed; **never** `--force` without explicit user request |

After push: report remote, branch, and commits pushed.

## Safety

- NEVER update git config
- NEVER `--no-verify`, force push, or hard reset unless user explicitly requests
- NEVER force push to `main` or `master`
- NEVER amend unless user asked and HEAD was not pushed
- One logical change per commit
- NEVER commit or push secrets (`.env`, credentials)

